Productivity

Productivity statistics show the number of active ZMWs (holes). Prod.Other resp P2 shows ZMWs that cannot be read reliably, most likely because it has more than one bound polymerase complex that produces cross-talk.

Overloading (high P2) can result in shorter polymerase reads.

shortmagbead_loadingprod.Emptyprod.Productiveprod.Otherprod.UndefinedP0P1P2
1M16530false288390350248801058881080136.0%62.7%1.3%

Internal Control Reads

Control reads are spiked in the run to assess sequencing quality and detect instrument/chemistry issues. These are aligned against a known genome to determine the error rate.

Length

shortcountcount.relmeanmean.relmedianmedian.rel
1M1653035840%11017393%7864293%
Showing 1 to 1 of 1 entries

Ratio of control read count to total productive ZMWs, mean and median control read length and comparison to sample polymerase read lengths. Truncated control reads indicate sequencing problems, e.g. chemistry, but also overloading of the SMRTcell (compare productivity numbers). Control reads longer than your sample polymerase reads indicate sample problems.

Quality

shortmeansdmedian
1M165300.910.020.91
Showing 1 to 1 of 1 entries

Control read quality is another indicator for sequencing quality. Low quality (<.85) might also indicate overloading (compare productivity numbers).

Polymerase Reads

Polymerase reads are reads within each ZMW (hole) that can consist of multiple passes of the fragment/insert.

shortcountsummeann50q05medianq95max
1M165305006105592497974073118,355.082421741,465.0084,261.00298,314.00510275

Number of polymerase reads (count) should correspond to P1 (productive ZMWs). sum shows the total number of basepairs; additionally various length statistics.

Yield in number of reads (left) and total number of basepairs.

Number of total polymerase reads count and total bp sum vs polymerase reads with at least one full pass (cx==3). This is mostly interesting for consensus applications (Iso-Seq, Amplicons) and expected to be very low for long inserts.

Polymerase read length statistics.

Yield vs Length

Passes/Context

Each polymerase read can pass multiple times over the insert/fragment, producing multiple subreads per ZMW (hole). Only full passes over the insert (cx==3) are counted; pass count 0 means that no or only one of the adaptors (left or right) was read. Partial subreads can still be used for circular consensus, if there is at least one or more full passes (depending on the cutoff parameters you use).

short min q05 q25 median q75 q95 max
M16530 0 0 0 5 18 57 1090

Number of passes per ZMW. Shorter libraries will have more passes. Very long libraries will likely have only 1 pass (resp. maybe not even one full pass).

Boxplot for pass counts.

Histogram truncated at 20 passes

Context Flag

The context flag shows for each subread whether no adapter (0), left (1) or right (2) or both (3) adapters could be read. Only CX flag 3 indicates a complete subread (end-to-end). Again, with very long libraries we do not expect many, if any, reads with CX flag 3.

Length statistics within each CX flag bin.

NoBloomCategorizer

We try to align a subsample of subreads (only one per ZMW) against some common genomes using minimap2.

short best_filter rate_unique rate_shared
M16530 noMatch 1 0

Subreads

Longest Subread

Longest subread shows only one subread per polymerase read/ZMW - the longest one (duh). This is the closest we get to “independent observations” (since all other subreads will have (part of) the same sequence).
